<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEBATE OVER THE CHURCH AND CELIBACY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For 35 years I have taught in Catholic schools, and I have worked closely with 
the clergy. 
</P>
<P>
Celibacy does not mean isolation. Priests are fully aware of the many struggles 
in family lives, traumas among the secular and their own personal sacrifices. 
</P>
<P>
Who was with me in intensive care unit, buried my parents, married my son and 
recently buried my oldest child? A priest! 
</P>
<P>
We would be honored to set his place at our table and dine on Christmas or any 
day that another family isn't in need. 
</P>
<P>
Do not stereotype the lonely ones who may prefer to isolate themselves on the 
few occasions they have. Even Christmas. 
</P>
<P>
MARY HELEN CHAMBERS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
