<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sawallisch to Philly: German impresario Wolfgang Sawallisch, whose association 
with the Philadelphia Orchestra dates back 24 years, Wednesday was named 
musical director of the orchestra. Sawallisch, director of Germany's Bavarian 
State Opera in Munich, will take over the podium in the 1993-94 season. He 
replaces Riccardo Muti, who will end a 12-year reign with the Philadelphia 
Orchestra after the 1992 season. BETH KLEID 
</P>
