<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Winged Figure' in Laguna: Artist Jim Morphesis' controversial painting, 
"Winged Figure," which was rejected by the John Wayne Museum of Art because 
airport officials found it unsuitable, will be on display at the Laguna Art 
Museum. 
</P>
<P>
Museum director Charles Desmarais said he is showing it to "lift the gloomy 
veil" from the painting. The work, which was originally commissioned by the 
airport, is a nude portrait of the Greek figure Icarus. It will be on display 
at the museum from Sept. 28 to Dec. 16. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
