<P>
FLORIDA STATE MAY DECIDE BY NEXT WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florida State University President Bernard Sliger said Wednesday he hopes to 
announce the school's decision on moving to a new conference by the middle of 
next week, well ahead of a school-established timetable that allowed to the end 
of September. 
</P>
<P>
The Miami Herald reported Wednesday that Florida State is only waiting to be 
invited by the Atlantic Coast Conference. 
</P>
<P>
The Southeastern Conference has also been lobbying Florida State, but the ACC 
package is more lucrative, Sliger confirmed. 
</P>
<P>
Sliger said that no decision could be announced until the options are presented 
to the school's athletic board. That is expected today and a decision is 
expected next week. 
</P>
<P>
Florida State presently competes in the Metro Conference in all sports but 
football. The Seminoles are independent in football. 
</P>
<P>
Florida State could be competing in most sports by next year, although it would 
take several years before the school could play a full conference schedule in 
football. 
</P>
</TEXT>
