<HEADLINE>
<P>
ISRAEL CLOSES LEBANESE PORT, CUTS ROUTE TO IRAQ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TYRE, Lebanon 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israel has closed a port in southern Lebanon after discovering it was used to 
smuggle Israeli food supplies to Iraq through Lebanon, security officials said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
They said the port of Naqoura, at the Lebanese-Israeli border and inside 
Israel's self-declared security zone in the south, was shut after Israel 
discovered that food being sent to Christian East Beirut had ended up in 
Baghdad. 
</P>
<P>
The security officials said that the Israeli goods were repackaged in East 
Beirut under Lebanese labels and sent to Iraq through Syria and Jordan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
