<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
MARIJUANA PLANTS SEIZED, 3 ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura County Sheriff's Department on Tuesday confiscated about 400 
marijuana plants from a Thousand Oaks family suspected of growing them in a 
bedroom and a back yard, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Adrian Bertolotti, 40, was arrested on suspicion of cultivation and possession 
for sale and is being held in lieu of $100,000 bail. His mother, Anna, 58, and 
his wife Page, 28, were held on suspicion of the same charge but were later 
released on their own recognizance. 
</P>
<P>
Concluding a four-month investigation, deputies served a search warrant in the 
500 block of Shenandoah Street about 6:30 p.m. Tuesday and found two separate 
marijuana gardens, said Sgt. Gary Pentis of the narcotics division. KIRSTEN LEE 
SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
