<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH PASADENA PUTS THE BITE ON NAIL SALONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HIRANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nail salons looking for a toehold in South Pasadena may be out of luck soon. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Amedee Richards suggested at last week's council meeting that the 
city investigate the possibility of limiting the number of certain types of 
commercial enterprises in South Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Richards said he would like to see a "balancing of the nature of the businesses 
we have here." 
</P>
<P>
He cited a recent survey by the South Pasadena Chamber of Commerce, which found 
that there are 18 hair and nail salons, 16 fast-food restaurants, 15 
dry-cleaning shops and seven video rental stores in the 3.4-square-mile city. 
</P>
<P>
The matter was referred to the Planning Commission for further study. STEVE 
HIRANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Nails 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
