<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SIERRA MADRE; 
</P>
<P>
CITY MAY NEED TO BUY WATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If the drought persists through the winter, the city will be forced to buy 
additional water, Mayor George Maurer said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Since June, the city has enacted a voluntary conservation program to reduce 
water consumption by 10%. But if the voluntary measures aren't enough, Sierra 
Madre may adopt a mandatory conservation program by next March, Maurer said. 
</P>
<P>
The city offers free water conservation kits and a list of conservation tips 
for residents at City Hall, 232 W. Sierra Madre Blvd. 
</P>
