<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
MORE PARKING METERS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council unanimously approved the installation of about 600 parking 
meters on seven streets. 
</P>
<P>
The additional meters, to be installed on streets including Washington, 
Sepulveda, Culver and Robertson boulevards, are expected to generate $80,000 
annually. 
</P>
<P>
The council also authorized $27,000 to pay for a community services officer for 
meter collection. The meters, which will be installed over a three-month 
period, are expected to produce $140,000 in parking violation fines. 
</P>
<P>
Affected businesses will be notified of a public hearing that will be held 
before installation of the new meters. 
</P>
<P>
The city will also remove poles that were installed two years ago without 
meters along Washington Boulevard between Zanja and Girard streets. 
</P>
