<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
PREFERENTIAL PARKING PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to resident complaints, the City Council has directed city staff to 
devise a system of preferential resident parking on Keystone and Coombs 
avenues. 
</P>
<P>
Residents of Keystone Avenue complained of a continuous parking spillover from 
the nearby Los Angeles County offices during business hours. 
</P>
<P>
Although police say they have increased enforcement, residents said there has 
been no difference. 
</P>
<P>
Residents of streets near Veterans Memorial Park, including Coombs Avenue, also 
complained of excess parking from the park. They complained to council members 
that park visitors were changing from business clothes to athletic attire on 
their front lawns. They asked the council to extend the weekday, daytime 
parking restrictions so that park users would be affected. 
</P>
<P>
The new parking guidelines will be presented at the council meeting Sept. 24. 
</P>
