<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
PERMIT PARKING APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has adopted an ordinance establishing a preferential-parking 
zone on 16th and 17th streets between Montana and Alta avenues. 
</P>
<P>
The zone establishes one-hour parking between 9 a.m. and 9 p.m. Monday through 
Saturday, except by permit. 
</P>
<P>
Merchants who have businesses, including haircutting and retail sales, on 
Montana Avenue complained that a one-hour limit would be insufficient for their 
customers. But the council rejected the merchants' request for two-hour or 
90-minute parking. 
</P>
<P>
The council also adopted an ordinance that establishes a preferential-parking 
zone on 25th Street between Santa Monica Boulevard and Broadway. Parking will 
be by permit only. 
</P>
