<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
MAIN STREET ZONING CHANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After seeing that the west end of Main Street isn't destined to become an 
automobile row after all, the City Council decided Monday to change the zoning 
back to general commercial. 
</P>
<P>
Assistant City Manager P. Michael Paules said in a report that the automobile 
zoning was established in 1986 when the city's General Plan was revised. 
However, Paules said the city has since realized the area is unsuitable for an 
auto strip, in part because of the shallowness of the lots. 
</P>
<P>
Paules said the change means businesses other than automobile dealerships will 
not have to obtain a conditional-use permit from the city to operate in the 
area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
