<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
5% RAISE FOR POLICE WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council agreed Monday to give members of the Police Employees' Assn. a 
5% raise retroactive to July 5. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager Kevin Murphy said the city and association, which represents 
civilian police employees, will reopen contract negotiations in six months 
after a study to determine if association members have higher levels of 
responsibility than other, comparably paid city employees. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy said the city is also close to signing a two-year agreement with the 
Police Officers Assn., which represents sworn officers. 
</P>
<P>
On Aug. 20, the council agreed to give fire employees a 5% raise for six months 
and to give all other city employees two 5% raises during the course of a 
two-year contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
