WESTSIDE DIGEST: HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
AIDS DISCUSSIONS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The public policy division of AIDS Project Los Angeles will hold the first in a 
series of public forums to address HIV-related political issues from 7 to 9:30 
p.m. Tuesday in room 140 of the AIDs Project Los Angeles' Nancy Cole Sawaya 
Center, 6721 Romaine St. 
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed include government policy on HIV, AIDS discrimination, 
legislation, and funding for AIDS programs and services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
