<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
BAN ON HOUSE ADDITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Homeowners who want to add a second story may have to wait until February 
because the City Council has decided to extend an urgency ordinance that 
temporarily prohibits such additions to single-family homes. 
</P>
<P>
The extension, approved Tuesday, will be in effect until Feb. 1, to give city 
staff members move time to study the issue. However, if the study is finished 
before Feb. 1, the moratorium may be lifted earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The ban went into effect July 24 to allow the city to determine whether new 
regulations are needed to ensure that second-story additions do not infringe on 
the rights of neighboring properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
