<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
SIGN ORDINANCE GETS OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Merchants will be able to fly promotional and seasonal banners for up to 63 
days a year, under a sign ordinance that received preliminary approval from the 
City Council Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
If the ordinance receives final approval Sept. 25, banners for special events 
could stay up for 21 consecutive days three times a year. Previously, banners 
were only allowed for 40 days a year, and they could not be flown for more than 
30 consecutive days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
