<HEADLINE>
<P>
SATURDAY'S HEROES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following are last week's top collegiate football performances by South Bay 
high school graduates: 
</P>
<P>
 Fred Gatlin, Nevada (Reno), sophomore: The former Carson High quarterback 
completed 17 of 28 passes for 266 yards and three touchdowns in a 55-14 victory 
over Northern Arizona to move into sixth on the school's all-time passing list. 
He was named Big Sky Conference Player of the Week. 
</P>
<P>
Treamelle Taylor, Nevada (Reno), senior: The former Hawthorne wide receiver had 
five catches for 103 yards, including a 78-yard touchdown from Gatlin, in the 
Wolf Pack's victory. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Craver, Fresno State, senior: The former El Camino College running back 
carried the ball 31 times for 175 yards and touchdowns of one and 61 yards in a 
24-17 victory over New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
Niu Sale, Missouri, junior: The former Bishop Montgomery and El Camino 
defensive back scored on a 52-yard punt return in a 20-19 loss to Texas 
Christian. It was Missouri's first punt return for a touchdown since 1978. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Treggs, UC Berkeley, junior: The former Carson wide receiver had three 
catches for 55 yards, including a 31-yard touchdown from quarterback Mike 
Pawlawski, in a 28-12 victory over Wisconsin 
</P>
<P>
Chris Maumalanga, Kansas, freshman: The former Bishop Montgomery defensive 
lineman recovered a fumble and helped the Jayhawks limit Oregon State to 44 
yards rushing in a 38-12 victory. 
</P>
<P>
Deon Figures, Colorado, sophomore: The former Serra cornerback had three 
unassisted tackles and three assists in a 21-17 victory over Stanford. 
</P>
</TEXT>
