</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The following are capsule reviews of some of the better restaurants recently 
visited by our critics: 
</P>
<P>
The Sportsman Restaurant and Cocktail Lounge is a throwback to the 1950s and 
'60s when it was one of the "special occasion" restaurants in Ventura. Although 
its prices might have changed with the times, the quality of its steaks and 
chops has not. The Sportsman is at 50 S. California St., Ventura, 643-2851. 
Open 11 a.m.-10 p.m. Monday-Friday, 11 a.m.-11 p.m. Saturday, 9 a.m.-2 p.m. for 
breakfast and lunch on Sunday, 5 p.m.-10 p.m. for dinner. Lunch for two, food 
only, $12-$20. Dinner for two, food only, $25-$46. 
</P>
<P>
The owners of Jag's India House call their Northern Indian cooking "royal Mogul 
cuisine." The hot fresh breads alone are worth the trip to the restaurant. 
There are dozens of versions of curries, from a fabulous shrimp masala to a 
lamb rogan josh. Jag's India House, 860 Hampshire, Suite U, Westlake Village, 
(805) 373-6266. Lunch 11:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. Tuesday-Friday; dinner 5:30-10 
p.m. Tuesday-Sunday. Wine and Beer. Parking lot. MasterCard and Visa. Dinner 
for two, food only, $30-$50. 
</P>
<P>
MK's is hot and cold. Hot in that it's frequently packed, cool as an oasis on a 
summer afternoon. Some dishes are very, very good, notably the seafood Vera 
Cruz and the "grazing platter" of grilled vegetables, grains, soft cheese, 
chutney and salsa. The bread is great, and when it is dessert time you'll go 
far before finding a better apricot cobbler. MK's is at 139 Ojai Ave., Ojai, 
640-8001. Breakfast 8-11 a.m. Monday, Wednesday-Friday; until noon 
Saturday-Sunday. Lunch 11:30 a.m.-2:30 p.m. Monday, Wednesday-Friday; noon-2:30 
p.m. Saturday-Sunday. Dinner 5-10 p.m. Wednesday-Monday. Meal for two, food 
only, $26-$58. 
</P>
<P>
Downey's is expensive, and sometimes it's worth it. The duck, no matter how 
prepared, is excellent. Add some of Downey's outstanding appetizers, such as 
the grilled squab, and flawless desserts, the Belgian chocolate marquis, for 
example, and you'll avoid the pitfalls -- overcooked fish and undistinguished 
beef and lamb dishes. Downey's is at 1305 State St., Santa Barbara, (805) 
966-5006. Dinner Tuesday to Sunday from 5:3O p.m. Dinner for two, food only, 
$65 to $80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
