COMMUNITY DIGEST: NORWALK; 
</P>
<P>
MANAGER GETS CONTRACT EXTENSION, PAY RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Norwalk City Council has extended the contract of City Manager Richard R. 
Powers by two years and raised his salary 26%, from $89,675 to $113,300 a year. 
</P>
<P>
The council also gave Powers a $7,500 bonus, which will be placed in a deferred 
compensation account, for outstanding performance during the past year. 
</P>
<P>
Powers' original three-year contract, made in 1988, was extended by two years 
and will expire in July, 1993. All of the council members touted Powers' work 
for the city. Powers said his proudest achievements include eliminating a 
$3.3-million annual operating deficit the city faced at the time he became city 
manager. 
</P>
