<TEXT>
<P>
Firm Honors Preservationist: Redmond, Wash.-based outdoor clothing manufacturer 
Eddie Bauer has chosen an Oregon rancher, nature book author and founder of the 
Institute of Range and the American Mustang for its first Heroes of the Earth 
award. 
</P>
<P>
Dayton O. (Hawk) Hyde, 65, founded the nonprofit institute, aimed at helping 
save wild horses, in 1987. Its first two refuges, at the institute's 
headquarters in Hot Springs, S.D., total more than 50,000 acres. Hyde is also 
founder of Operation Stronghold, a nonprofit corporation that has helped 
landowners establish wildlife habitats on more than 4 million acres of private 
property. 
</P>
