<P>
Lawyer Pleads Guilty to Fraud: An attorney formerly with a prestigious 
corporate law firm pleaded guilty to selling inside information about planned 
takeovers in a multimillion-dollar trading scheme. 
</P>
<P>
Steven L. Glauberman, 39, of Manhattan, was charged last month with four counts 
of conspiracy, securities fraud and wire fraud. He pleaded guilty to two counts 
of securities fraud and one of wire fraud. He faces a maximum fine of $250,000 
and up to five years in prison on each count when sentenced Dec. 21. 
