</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMD Loses Patent Suit Over Chips: In a case that breaks new legal ground, 
Advanced Micro Devices has lost a patent infringement lawsuit brought by 
Brooktree Corp. of San Diego. A U.S. District Court jury found that AMD 
violated three of Brooktree's patents and also infringed on the company's 
rights to protect chip layout designs under a 1984 law. The Brooktree suit has 
been closely watched as the first major test of the Semiconductor Chip 
Protection Act, which made illegal the use of photographic techniques and other 
forms of copying chip designs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
