<P>
Brazil to Open Computer Market: The Brazilian government said it would open its 
computer market to imports, ending a controversial policy adopted in 1984 to 
protect its fledgling computer industry that had prompted U.S. trade 
retaliation. Under the latest plan, imports of only 30 types of products, 
mainly in the area of microcomputers, will be prohibited until 1992. All other 
computer products will be allowed in, although import tariffs have not yet been 
set. 
