<P>
2 LOTTO TICKETS SHARE JACKPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two lucky tickets had all six winning numbers in Wednesday night's California 
Lottery "Lotto 6/53" drawing, each winning $16.15 million, lottery officials 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
The tickets split a $32.3-million jackpot. 
</P>
<P>
They were purchased in Santa Ana and Garden Grove, lottery officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Six tickets had five numbers plus the bonus number, with each worth $177,952. 
They shared a prize pool of $1.06 million. Those were bought in San Ramon, San 
Diego, Poway, Oxnard and two in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
There were 273 tickets that had five of six numbers, each winning $3,911. Those 
tickets also share a $1.06 million prize pool. 
</P>
<P>
Sales from Saturday night to Wednesday's drawing were $19.4 million. The 
estimated jackpot for Saturday night's drawing is $4 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
