<TEXT>
<P>
The National Assn. of Broadcasters at its annual meeting announced a campaign 
to send radio receivers and batteries to American troops serving in the Persian 
Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
Westinghouse Broadcasting Co.'s Group W Radio division will lead a fund-raising 
campaign and the Armed Forces Radio and Television Service will distribute the 
radios and batteries, the association said. 
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to get as many radios to as many troops as we possibly can, with a 
target of 25,000 receivers with batteries," said Lynn Christian, an association 
senior vice president. "We think radio can play a very important role keeping 
our fighting people in touch with the world." 
