K MART TO BUY INTO OFFICEMAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TROY, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
K mart Corp., which recently announced plans to revamp its entire discount 
store chain over the next few years, today said that it has agreed to buy a 22% 
stake in office supply superstore chain OfficeMax for undisclosed terms. 
</P>
<P>
OfficeMax, a privately held chain based in Cleveland, also agreed to acquire 
the Office Square business of a K mart subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
Under the cash deal, K mart also has the right to boost its stake in OfficeMax. 
</P>
<P>
"Large size office supply stores represent an exciting growth opportunity for K 
mart. . . . These superstores are expected to capture an increasing share of 
the growing office supply and equipment market in the years ahead," K mart 
Chairman Joseph Antonini said. 
</P>
<P>
OfficeMax President Michael Feuer said the cash infusion and the five Office 
Square stores it will acquire from K mart will allow OfficeMax to continue its 
rapid expansion. 
</P>
