<P>
REEDY WAS DRUNK, OFFICIAL SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORT CRANE, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A medical examiner testified today that William Reedy's blood-alcohol level was 
well above the legal limit when the pickup truck he is accused of driving 
crashed and former major-league manager Billy Martin was killed. 
</P>
<P>
Onondaga County Medical Examiner Erik Mitchell told a Town of Fenton Court jury 
that Reedy's blood-alcohol level as measured at a hospital immediately after 
the crash was 0.16%. The legal limit in New York for driving while intoxicated 
is 0.10.% 
</P>
