DOUBLE-HEADER AT FAIRPLEX PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A stakes double-header highlights action at Fairplex Park in Pomona on Friday 
when the $40,000-added Beau Brummel Stakes and $35,000-added Las Ninas Stakes 
share the bill on the 13-race card. 
</P>
<P>
There will be one non-wagering race, the first trial to the Pacific Coast 
Quarter Horse Breeders Assn. Futurity, at noon. Later in the day, 2-year-old 
colts and geldings meet in the Beau Brummel at 6 1/2 furlongs. Ten horses are 
entered, including an entry. 
</P>
<P>
The Las Ninas gives 3-year-old fillies that have not won an added-money event a 
stakes opportunity over 6 1/2 furlongs. Eight are entered. 
